Default Method :
 the method define using default key word in an interface that has as implementation

 EX:

public interface MyInterface{
 
    default void m1(){
       //implementation
    }

 }

 -default method can be ovverridden

Why introduce
- For backward compatibility - If new method add in interface then all classes which implement that they should be ovverride, so for this cause default method comes. Due to default we only ovverride whenever required only.

Diamond Problem:
If two interface have same method name, same parameter and one class implement both interface, then we need to compulsory ovverride, and need to specify which method need to be call EX. Calculator.super.calculator(a, b)

--------------------***-------------------------
public interface Calculator {
	default int calculator(int a, int b) {
		return a+b;
	}
}
--------------------***-------------------------
public interface Calculator1 {
	default int calculator(int a, int b) {
		return a*b;
	}
}
--------------------***-------------------------
public class CalculatorImpl implements Calculator,Calculator1{
	@Override
	public int calculator(int a, int b) {
		// TODO Auto-generated method stub
		return Calculator.super.calculator(a, b);
	}
}
