Static methods in interface in java 8:

-main purpose is that only interface have implementation , this not change by any class by ovverride it.

-If we declare static method then we should need to give implementation , not able to create abstract static method
-we can able to call one static method from another static method 

Points from vidio:
-static methods belongs to interface, not to the child class
-static methods cannot be ovverridden
-An interface can have multiple static methods
-static methods must have a body
-static method can call another static method but not a default method
-it can be invoked by interface's name

--------------------***-------------------------
public interface Payment{

   default int calculator(int a, int b) {
		if (isValidAmount(a, a)) {
			return a + b;
		} else {
			return 0;
		}
	}

   static boolean isValidAmount(int amount, int amount2) {
		logInTime();
		if (amount > 0 && amount2 > 0) {
			return true;
		}
		return false;
	}

	static String logInTime() {
		return "LogInTime";
	}

}

