Optional Class:
It introduce in java8 where main funtion is to handle null checks 
-May or may not contain value


Methods cover:
1.isPresent - optionalUser.isPresent() ----retrun true or false - true if value present
2.OPtional.of(T);   Optional.of(user); ----return OPtional<T> - not handle null checks
3.OPtional.ofNullable(T);   Optional.of(user); ----return OPtional<T> - handle null checks--if null it return empty optional
4.get();  --optionalUser.get();   it return T ---User user = optionalUser.get();  if optionalUser is null then it throw exception
5.empty();  --Optional.empty(); ---returns empty Optional Object
6.ifPresent - optionalUser.ifPresent(user->System.out.println("")); - it execute only when value present, it takes argument as Consumer
7.orElse(T); - User user = optionalUser2.orElse(new User(-1, "Default")); System.out.println(""); 
8.orElseGet(Consumer T);  User user = optionalUser.orElseGet(()->new User(-1, "Default"));
9.orElseThrow(); User user = optionalUser.orElseThrow(); ---throw exception when value is null
10.OPtional.ofNullable(T);   Optional.ofNullable(user); ----return OPtional<T> -  handle null checks




