Strem methods:

findFirst() -It is a terminal method that returns the first element of the stream - returns object in optional

anyMatch() - It is terminal method that returns true if any element matches a given condition.  

allMatch() - It is a terminal method that returns true if all elements match a given condition.

noneMatch() - It is a terminal method that returns true if no elements match a given condition.

sorted() - It is Intermediate method that returns a Stream with element sorted.
numbers.stream().sorted().forEach(System.out::println);

parallelStream() - 
It allows the stream to process elements in parallel making the processing faster.



